This is from Alan Field of SUPERVALU in Eden Prairie, Minnesota and
contains a zap to show system information at the bottom of the
OS/390 operator console.  This zap was taken from the IBM-MAIN
Internet forum.

Date: 97-12-08 09:52:46 EST
From:	alan.field@SUPERVALU.COM (Alan Field)
Sender:	IBM-MAIN@UA1VM.UA.EDU (IBM Mainframe Discussion List)
Reply-to:	IBM-MAIN@UA1VM.UA.EDU (IBM Mainframe Discussion List)
To:	IBM-MAIN@UA1VM.UA.EDU

We use a usermod to IEE163I (see bottom of console). It tells SYSRES
volser, address and OS release.

From: Alan Field <alan.field@SUPERVALU.COM>
Subject:      Re: How To Determine Operating Environment
To: IBM-MAIN@UA1VM.UA.EDU

$PICTURE.text:
Here is a snippet from the console:

                        SYS3D.BOOLE.T2BADATA.BKP
 00  08.30.47 JOB31326  TMS014  IEF234E K 03E6
 IEE612I CN=SVT2MSTR DEVNUM=0016 SYS=SVT2


 IEE163I MODE= RD-HNR401/0996-SP6.0.4

The mod affects the bottom line.  The "extra" space in the messages
is limited. I think this is as much text as can be added.  One
version of the zap used to have the SMF id, but with named consoles
(see the IEE612I) that feature became less useful.

Alan

LM00031A.text:
++ USERMOD (LM00031)        REWORK(1997001)
       /* MODIFY CONSOLE MSG IEE163I MODE= ...
          THIS VERSION SUPPORTS A 4 DIGIT UCB ADDRESS FOR SYSRES
       */ .
++ VER (Z038) FMID(HBB6603) .
++ ZAP (IEECVETD) .
* MOD TO CHANGE CONSOLE IEE163I MODE= MESSAGE FOR NEAT INFO
NAME IEECVET1 IEECVETD
 EXPAND IEECVETD(64)
VER 02E6 9108,C02A
VER 04F8 5C5C,40C9                  ** PATCH AREA
*
REP 02E6 47F0,A4F6                  B     PATCH AREA
REP 04F8 41F0,A500                  LA    R15,*+10     31 BIT ADDR
REP 04FC 56F0,A546                  O     R15,=A(X'80000000')
REP 0500 0B0F                       BSM   R0,R15
REP 0502 58E0,0010                  L     R14,16
REP 0506 58F0,E030                  L     R15,48(,R14)
REP 050A 9260,2010                  MVI   16(R2),C'-'
REP 050E D205,2011,F01C             MVC   17(6,R2),28(R15) SYSRES
REP 0514 9261,2017                  MVI   23(R2),C'/'
REP 0518 F342,2018,F004             UNPK  24(5,R2),4(3,R15)
REP 051E 41F0,A522                  LA    R15,*+6          24 BIT MODE
REP 0522 0B0F                       BSM   R0,R15
REP 0524 D403,2018,A55A             NC    24(4,R2),=X'0F0F0F0F'
REP 052A DC03,2018,A54A             TR    24(4,R2),=C'0123456789ABCDEF'
REP 0530 9260,201C                  MVI   28(R2),C'-'
REP 0534 41F0,0028                  LA    R15,40
REP 0538 1BEF                       SR    R14,R15
REP 053A D207,201D,E000             MVC   29(8,R2),0(R14)  VERSION
REP 0540 9108,C02A                  TM    42(,R12),X'08'
REP 0544 47F0,A2E8                  B     744(,R10)
REP 0548 8000,0000                  =A(X'80000000')
REP 054C F0F1,F2F3,F4F5,F6F7        =C'01234567'
REP 0554 F8F9,C1C2,C3C4,C5C6        =C'89ABCDEF'
REP 055C 0F0F,0F0F                  =X'0F0F0F0F'
